 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Mumon’s Commentary</h3><p>If anyone can open one eye at this point and say a word of Zen, he is qualified to repay the four gratifications, and, not only that, he can save all sentient beings under him.\nBut if he cannot say such a word of Zen, he should turn back to his tail.</p><h3 id=\"mumons-poem\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mumons-poem\" aria-label=\"mumons poem permalink\" class=\"no-tufte-underline before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Mumon’s Poem</h3><ul style=\"list-style-type:none\">\n<li> If the buffalo runs, he will fall into the trench;  </li>\n<li> If he returns, he will be butchered.   </li>\n<li> That little tail </li>\n<li> Is a very strange thing. </li>\n</ul></section>\n<section><h2 id=\"the-short-stafflabel-forsd-first-seen-in-goedel-classmargin-toggle-sidenote-numberlabelinput-typecheckbox-idsd-first-seen-in-goedel-classmargin-toggle-span-classsidenotefirst-seen-in-gödel-escher-bachspan\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-short-stafflabel-forsd-first-seen-in-goedel-classmargin-toggle-sidenote-numberlabelinput-typecheckbox-idsd-first-seen-in-goedel-classmargin-toggle-span-classsidenotefirst-seen-in-g%C3%B6del-escher-bachspan\" aria-label=\"the short stafflabel forsd first seen in goedel classmargin toggle sidenote numberlabelinput typecheckbox idsd first seen in goedel classmargin toggle span classsidenotefirst seen in gödel escher bachspan permalink\" class=\"no-tufte-underline before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Short Staff<label for=\"sd-first-seen-in-goedel\" class=\"margin-toggle sidenote-number\"></label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"sd-first-seen-in-goedel\" class=\"margin-toggle\" /><span class=\"sidenote\">First seen in Gödel, Escher, Bach</span></h2><h3 id=\"kōan-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#k%C5%8Dan-1\" aria-label=\"kōan 1 permalink\" class=\"no-tufte-underline before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Kōan</h3><p>Shuzan held out his short staff and said: “If you call this a short staff, you oppose its reality.\nIf you do not call it a short staff, you ignore the fact.\nNow what do you wish to call this?”</p><h3 id=\"mumons-commentary-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mumons-commentary-1\" aria-label=\"mumons commentary 1 permalink\" class=\"no-tufte-underline before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Mumon’s Commentary</h3><p>If you call this a short staff, you oppose its reality.\nIf you do not call it a short staff, you ignore the fact.\nIt cannot be expressed with words and it cannot be expressed without words.\nNow say quickly what it is.</p><h3 id=\"mumons-poem-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mumons-poem-1\" aria-label=\"mumons poem 1 permalink\" class=\"no-tufte-underline before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Mumon’s Poem</h3><ul style=\"list-style-type:none\">\n<li> Holding out the short staff, </li>\n<li> He gave an order of life or death. </li>\n<li> Positive and negative interwoven, </li>\n<li> Even Buddhas and patriarchs cannot escape this attack. </li>\n</ul></section>\n<section><h2 id=\"the-reflected-moonlabel-forsd-first-seen-in-goedel-classmargin-toggle-sidenote-numberlabelinput-typecheckbox-idsd-first-seen-in-goedel-classmargin-toggle-span-classsidenotefirst-seen-in-gödel-escher-bachspan\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-reflected-moonlabel-forsd-first-seen-in-goedel-classmargin-toggle-sidenote-numberlabelinput-typecheckbox-idsd-first-seen-in-goedel-classmargin-toggle-span-classsidenotefirst-seen-in-g%C3%B6del-escher-bachspan\" aria-label=\"the reflected moonlabel forsd first seen in goedel classmargin toggle sidenote numberlabelinput typecheckbox idsd first seen in goedel classmargin toggle span classsidenotefirst seen in gödel escher bachspan permalink\" class=\"no-tufte-underline before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Reflected Moon<label for=\"sd-first-seen-in-goedel\" class=\"margin-toggle sidenote-number\"></label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"sd-first-seen-in-goedel\" class=\"margin-toggle\" /><span class=\"sidenote\">First seen in Gödel, Escher, Bach</span></h2><p>Chiyono studied Zen for many years under Bukkō of Engaku.\nStill, she could not attain the fruits of meditation.\nAt last one moonlight night she was carrying water in an old wooden pail girded with bamboo.\nThe bamboo broke, and the bottom fell out of the pail.\nAt that moment, she was set free.\nChiyono said, “No more water in the pail, no more moon in the water.”</p></section>","frontmatter":{"title":"A collection of kōans","subtitle":"Kōans that I find thought-provoking","date":"2022-04-17","lastupdated":"2022-04-17","topics":["notes","zen","buddhism"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/notes/misc/koans/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/notes/lectures/sapolosky-robert-human-behavioral-biology/"},"frontmatter":{"topics":["notes","lectures","biology","evolution"],"title":"Sapolosky, Robert; Human Behavioral Biology","layout":"post","published":true,"booknote":null}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/notes/books/novels/carroll-lewis-alice-in-wonderland/"},"frontmatter":{"topics":["notes","lectures","biology","evolution"],"title":"Carroll, Lewis; Alice in Wonderland","layout":"post","published":true,"booknote":null}}}},
